<DOC><DOCNO> AP880223-0245 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-23-88 0910EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Japan-Business     02-23 0198</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Japan-Business,0204</SECOND><HEAD>Matsushita To Open New U.S. Company</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Matsushita Electric Industrial Corp., one of theworld's largest consumer electronics manufacturers, has announcedplans to set up a new firm in the United States in April for salesand maintainance of factory automation machines, a Japanese newsreport said.   The new firm, Panasonic Factory Automation Co., a division ofMatsushita Electric Corp. of America, will pave the way forMatsushita's further expansion of factory automation business inNorth America and localization of the development of computersoftware used for factory automation, Kyodo News Service saidTuesday.   Matsushita officials did not answer repeated telephone calls totheir offices Tuesday night.   Sales of factory automation equipment have been handled byPanasonic Industrial Co., but the rapid growth of the factoryautomation market in North America led the parent company to set upa new firm dedicated solely to that purpose, Kyodo said.   Panansonic Factory Automation Co., which will sell industrialrobots and installation devices for electronics parts, aims toboost its sales of 6.5 billion yen, or $58 million, in the fiscalyear ending March 31, 1988 _ and by five times within five years,Kyodo said.</TEXT></DOC>